ISIDINGO actress Noluthando &ldquo;Nolly&rdquo; Meje has allegedly found love.The star, who plays Zukisa in the SABC3 soapie, is allegedly dating actor Neo Ntlatleng.The two allegedly couldn&rsquo;t keep their hands off each at the recent South African Film and Television Awards in Sun City, North West.&ldquo;On Thursday night, at the technical awards ceremony, the two sat together. When Neo went on stage as part of The Road cast who won the Best TV Soap Award, Nolly kept taking pictures of him,&rdquo; said one source.When called for comment, Nolly laughed off the claims and said: &ldquo;We&rsquo;re not dating, I have no man. We work together on a production. You&rsquo;re going to get him in trouble with his girlfriend with this story.&rdquo;But another source claimed Nolly seemed happy and content, and love was good for her.&ldquo;If there&rsquo;s one person who hasn&rsquo;t let fame affect her, it&rsquo;s Nolly. She&rsquo;s also a private person and she&rsquo;s dating another private person.&nbsp;&ldquo;Their love match is beautiful and we hope they go far,&rdquo; said another source.Nolly has been in showbiz since 2011. She&rsquo;s built her name as a singer and actress, and is now one of TV&rsquo;s most recognised faces.Neo is a former child star, who has been making moves behind the scenes and in front of the camera.He has acted in Soul City, The Road, Zone 14 and 90 Plein Street. Little is know about his private life.&nbsp;Neo could not be reached for comment at the time of going to print.